@node DISCLAIMER "Disclaimer"

Disclaimer
----------

Certainly  Reflex isn't bugfree, but to my knowledge it will not in any way
harm  your system. The only fatal error Reflex has had was removed almost a
year  ago,  and  Reflex hasn't been the cause of a system crash for months.
For the more than one year I've been using Reflex in its more or less final
state not one single file has been deleted without it being on purpose.

Still  I  will  naturally  not  guarantee  anything. If Reflex crashes your
system  or  deletes files that shouldn't have been deleted, I'm very sorry,
but please do not blame me.

Often  errors  are  the  cause  of  the  actions of the users - and not the
programmer's fault. Naturally this is not always true.

Anyway - use Reflex and its ARexx port at your own risk.

[À]
@endnode

